<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="here/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="mediacentre">
<head>
    <title>Information about the RDF Fepository</title>
</head>
<body>
<div metal:fill-slot="main">
    <p>
    RDF Repository is a repository for RDF/RSS feeds.
    </p>

    <p tal:condition="request/theme|nothing"
       tal:content="string:You've selected the ${request/theme} theme.
                    The result below is only for this theme."/>
    <ul>
        <li tal:repeat="data view/getRDFStats"
            tal:content="data/url" />
    </ul>

    <p>
    RDF Repository relies on plugins. Each plugin knows how to retrieve
    RDF/RSS files data from the repository it handles. When RDF Repository
    is asked for all feeds that are available it will forward the question
    to all registered plugins and will then merge the results.
    </p>

    <p>
    Registered plugins:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li tal:repeat="plugin view/getPluginNames"
            tal:content="plugin" />
    </ul>

</div>
</body>
</html>
